oninkrijk","East Harling, Norfolk, England":"East Harling, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Westerfield, Suffolk, England":"Westerfield, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Grundisburg, Suffolk, England":"Grundisburgh, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1297–1417":"about 1297–1417","1297–1340":"1297–1340","1328–1358":"1328–1358","1332–Male":"1332–Deceased","1346–1403":"1346–1403","1297–1417":"1297–1417","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1346":"1346","about 1328":"about 1328","1 Jul 1403":"1 July 1403","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1340":"1340","about 1332":"1332","about 1297":"about 1297","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","East Harling, Norfolk, England":"East Harling, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","of Westerfield, Suffolk, England":"Westerfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Grundisburg, Suffolk, England":"Grundisburgh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Weyland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans, Kurt.","German: variant of   Wieland  .","English: variant of   Wayland  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Wieland","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Erwin, Otto, Heinz, Dieter, Dietrich, Erdmann, Florian, Franz, Fritz, Gerhard.","German: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>wīg</i> ‘war’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, territory’. This name was borne by the supernaturally skilled smith of ancient Germanic folk legend, and for this reason it may in part have been given as a nickname to blacksmiths.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): presumably an adoption of the German surname."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret de Weyland was born about 1297, in Westerfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She married John De Herle I in 1340, in East Harling, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1417, in Grundisburgh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 121."},"et":{"about 1297–1417":"umbes 1297–1417","1297–1340":"1297–1340","1328–1358":"1328–1358","1332–Male":"1332–Surnud","1346–1403":"1346–1403","1297–1417":"1297–1417","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1346":"1346","about 1328":"umbes 1328","1 Jul 1403":"1. juuli 1403","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1340":"1340","about 1332":"1332","about 1297":"umbes 1297","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","East Harling, Norfolk, England":"East Harling, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Westerfield, Suffolk, England":"Westerfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Grundisburg, Suffolk, England":"Grundisburgh, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1297–1417":"noin 1297–1417","1297–1340":"1297–1340","1328–1358":"1328–1358","1332–Male":"1332–Kuollut","1346–1403":"1346–1403","1297–1417":"1297–1417","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1346":"1346","about 1328":"noin 1328","1 Jul 1403":"1. heinäkuuta 1403","1332":"1332","1297":"1297","1340":"1340","about 1332":"1332","about 1297":"noin 1297","1417":"1417","1328":"1328","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thetford, Norfolk, England":"Thetford, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","East Harling, Norfolk, England":"E